a disturbance erupted late saturday among more than 1,000 students on spring break, leaving four people with stab wounds and two police officers with injuries, authorities said. a car was missing after going off a ferry dock into the water
it's an all-out riot,'' said anthony lloyd, a coast guard spokesman in port aransas. ``they are setting cars on fire. people are hurt on the beach.''
the disturbance began when a motorist hit a girl on the beach at this popular gulf coast vacation spot and tried to leave the scene, said corpus christi department of public safety officer a.g. michniak
there was a hit-and-run accident on the beach that injured one,'' michniak said. ``the crowd stopped the car, took out the occupants and tipped it over and burned it.''
they stomped the car, broke all the glass out of it and flipped it over,'' said tom frazier, 22, a student at the university of texas
at least eight people were arrested, michniak said
