a jet with 78 people aboard made an emergency landing sunday after a section of its landing gear malfunctioned, and one wing caught fire briefly as it scraped the runway, officials said. no one was injured
the delta air lines boeing 727 was safely evacuated by emergency chutes after it landed about 4 p.m. at portland international airport, said port of portland spokeswoman sara roberts
flight 314 carried 71 passengers and a crew of seven, said david zielke, a delta spokesman
port of portland spokesman darrel buttice said the pilot was unable to lower the left wheel assembly, forcing the airplane to land on the remaining two sets of wheels, right rear and center front
emergency crews put out a small fire on the left wing, which scraped the runway as the airplane came to a halt, he said
it looked like he had everything under control and then as he started to get close to the ground, he ... looked like he just kind of leaned into that one side a little bit,'' said a witness, gary spencer
he landed and just immediately the fire equipment was right on top of him, spraying foam,'' spencer said. ``i didn't see any fire but i guess there was a little bit.''
inflatable yellow emergency chutes were deployed from the doorways, and passengers were evacuated from the airplane without incident, ms. roberts said. passengers were bused from the runway to the terminal
as far as we know, people are on their way home,'' she said
the flight originated in atlanta and made a stop in salt lake city before heading to portland, buttice said. news digest: boston-meet dukakis; mamelodi, south africa _ trading places; panama city _ panama canal; undated _ amnesty hoopla; columbus, ohio _ magruder-ethics; washington _ too big to fail; washington _ gesell profile; belgrade _ yugoslav contrasts; washington _ star wars; dover, del. _ hotel reunions; washington _ playwright king.</note>
